{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f323cd9-17bf-4307-9a1b-a299a2251481","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the migration is straightforward. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's essentially it. MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default** — `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting you *out* of it. Removing that property lets the SDK default kick in.\n\n### Other things to check:\n\n1. **CLI change** — use `dotnet test` as usual (supported since .NET SDK 8.0.4+), but you can also run the test executable directly.\n2. **Remove VSTest-specific packages** — if you explicitly reference `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, it's no longer needed with MSTest.Sdk.\n3. **Runsettings** — most `.runsettings` options work, but review any VSTest-specific adapter settings.\n4. **CI pipelines** — if you parse TRX output, add `--results-directory` and `--report-trx` to your `dotnet test` invocation, since TRX reporting is now opt-in.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d16c3198-d9f1-47df-b2e6-23e9ac3d6f09","outputTokens":293,"requestId":"A02D:17D0EF:C66D8D:E7392D:69FE866C"},"id":"62fd9156-92d6-49bd-94bd-4dd41708c23b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:57:24.642Z","parentId":"b73c00ce-f07c-4c64-930f-c1df8644fec5"}
